---

{% from "macros/course.njk" import activitySection, reviewSection,
   accordion, quizMC, tabSet, toolSection %}


{# ══ Activity 1 — Introduction ════════════════════════════════ #}

{% call activitySection(1, "So and Neither", "book") %}
<p>
  <strong>So</strong> and <strong>neither</strong> (or <em>nor</em>) are used to show that
  something is also true of another person or situation. They are a concise alternative
  to repeating the full verb phrase.
</p>
<div class="p-3 mb-3" style="background:#1a1a1a; border-left:4px solid #ff8c00; border-radius:0 0.375rem 0.375rem 0;">
  <p class="mb-1"><strong>Positive statement:</strong> <em>"I enjoy reading."</em></p>
  <p class="mb-0"><strong>Agreement:</strong> <em>"<span style="color:#ff8c00;">So do I.</span>"</em></p>
</div>
<div class="p-3" style="background:#1a1a1a; border-left:4px solid #ff8c00; border-radius:0 0.375rem 0.375rem 0;">
  <p class="mb-1"><strong>Negative statement:</strong> <em>"She doesn't like spicy food."</em></p>
  <p class="mb-0"><strong>Agreement:</strong> <em>"<span style="color:#ff8c00;">Neither do I.</span>"</em></p>
</div>
{% endcall %}


{# ══ Activity 2 — Patterns ════════════════════════════════════ #}

{% call activitySection(2, "Forming So/Neither Responses", "list-check") %}
<p class="mb-3">The auxiliary verb in the response must match the tense of the original statement.</p>

<div class="accordion" id="unit06-patterns">

  {% call accordion("acc-06-a", "So + auxiliary + I (positive agreement)") %}
  <table class="table table-sm table-dark table-bordered mt-2" style="font-size:0.875rem;">
    <thead><tr><th>Statement</th><th>Response</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>I am tired.</td><td>So am I.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>She works hard.</td><td>So do I.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>They have finished.</td><td>So have I.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>He can swim.</td><td>So can I.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>We will attend.</td><td>So will I.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% endcall %}

  {% call accordion("acc-06-b", "Neither + auxiliary + I (negative agreement)") %}
  <table class="table table-sm table-dark table-bordered mt-2" style="font-size:0.875rem;">
    <thead><tr><th>Statement</th><th>Response</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>I am not ready.</td><td>Neither am I.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>She doesn't drive.</td><td>Neither do I.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>They haven't replied.</td><td>Neither have I.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>He can't swim.</td><td>Neither can I.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>We won't be there.</td><td>Neither will I.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% endcall %}

  {% call accordion("acc-06-c", "Key rule: match the auxiliary") %}
  <p>
    The auxiliary verb in <em>So/Neither</em> must match the one in the original sentence.
    If the original uses <em>have</em>, so does the response. If it uses <em>did</em>, so
    does the response. Never use a different auxiliary.
  </p>
  <table class="table table-sm table-dark table-bordered mt-2" style="font-size:0.875rem;">
    <thead><tr><th>Correct</th><th>Incorrect</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>I worked hard. So did I. ✓</td><td>I worked hard. So do I. ✗</td></tr>
      <tr><td>She has left. So has she. ✓</td><td>She has left. So did she. ✗</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  {% endcall %}

</div>
{% endcall %}


{# ══ Activity 3 — Tool ════════════════════════════════════════ #}

{% call toolSection("Tool: So/Neither Generator") %}
<p class="mb-3">
  Type a positive or negative statement. The tool will generate the correct
  <em>So…</em> or <em>Neither…</em> response.
</p>
<p class="mb-3" style="font-size:0.875rem; color:#aaa;">
  <i class="bi bi-info-circle"></i>
  <strong>Try:</strong> <em>"I enjoy cooking."</em> &nbsp;or&nbsp; <em>"She can't drive."</em>
</p>

<div class="mb-2">
  <label class="tool-label" for="text-input">Your statement</label>
  <input type="text" id="text-input" class="tool-input"
         placeholder="Enter a statement…" aria-label="Statement input"
         oninput="changeInput(this.value)">
</div>

<div class="d-flex gap-2 mb-3">
  <button class="tool-btn" id="button" onclick="generate()" disabled>
    <i class="bi bi-arrow-right-circle"></i> Generate Response
  </button>
</div>

<div class="tool-label">Response</div>
<div id="result" class="tool-output" style="min-height:3rem;">
  <span style="color:#666; font-style:italic;">The so/neither response will appear here…</span>
</div>
{% endcall %}


{# ══ Activity 4 — Quiz ════════════════════════════════════════ #}

{% call activitySection(4, "Check Your Understanding", "patch-question") %}

{% call quizMC("quiz-06-a", "Complete the response: 'She has finished her essay.' '___'", 2,
   "'So have I' matches the auxiliary 'has' (present perfect) with 'have I', maintaining the same tense.") %}
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-a" value="0"> So do I.</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-a" value="1"> So did I.</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-a" value="2"> So have I.</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-a" value="3"> So am I.</label>
{% endcall %}

<div class="mt-4">
{% call quizMC("quiz-06-b", "'I can't play the piano.' Which response is correct?", 1,
   "'Neither can I' matches the modal 'can' from the negative statement. 'Neither' is used because the original statement is negative.") %}
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-b" value="0"> So can I.</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-b" value="1"> Neither can I.</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-b" value="2"> Neither do I.</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-b" value="3"> So do I.</label>
{% endcall %}
</div>

<div class="mt-4">
{% call quizMC("quiz-06-c", "When do you use 'neither' instead of 'so'?", 0,
   "'Neither' is used to agree with negative statements. 'So' is used to agree with positive ones.") %}
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-c" value="0"> When the original statement is negative</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-c" value="1"> When the original statement is in the past tense</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-c" value="2"> When you disagree with the statement</label>
  <label class="quiz-option"><input type="radio" name="quiz-06-c" value="3"> When the subject is a third person</label>
{% endcall %}
</div>

{% endcall %}


